With the current implementation, the `_pubsub` property will never be `None`. You can view several sections in the class making this check:
- https://github.com/celery/celery/pull/5145/files#diff-accb7090ee45fffb2262cbceeabef002R135
- https://github.com/celery/celery/pull/5145/files#diff-accb7090ee45fffb2262cbceeabef002R124
- https://github.com/celery/celery/pull/5145/files#diff-accb7090ee45fffb2262cbceeabef002R92

I would suggest the following:
- Create the Redis client and PubSub instance during initialization in the [start](https://github.com/celery/celery/pull/5145/files#diff-accb7090ee45fffb2262cbceeabef002L105) method.
- Have this property fetch the attribute from the thread local: 
```python
@property
def _pubsub(self):
    return getattr(self._thread, '_pubsub', None)
```

@thedrow does that sound logical? @sihrc I believe this approach will minimize the changes and effort as well.
